(Real Learning Application) Tj
T*
(In real study situations, students master Pronunciation by practising with tasks that) Tj
T*
(mirror stress patterns and sound distinctions. The topic becomes more meaningful when it) Tj
T*
(is linked to examples, revision drills, and exam-style questions that reflect how) Tj
T*
(English is assessed.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Examples) Tj
T*
(Worked Example 1) Tj
T*
(1. Start with an example based on contrasting minimal pairs with different vowel sounds.) Tj
T*
(2. Identify the exact idea in stress, vowel sounds, consonants, and clear articulation) Tj
T*
(that the question is testing.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct method for Pronunciation step by step without skipping reasoning.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the final answer and explain why it is correct.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Example 2) Tj
T*
(1. Choose a second example that still focuses on stress patterns and sound distinctions.) Tj
T*
(2. Break the task into smaller parts and link each part to the rule being used.) Tj
T*
(3. Point out how to avoid pronouncing words only by spelling while solving it.) Tj
T*
(4. Review the result and connect it back to the topic overview.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Common Mistakes) Tj
T*
(- Misunderstanding the core focus of Pronunciation: stress, vowel sounds, consonants,) Tj
T*
(and clear articulation.) Tj
T*
(- Pronouncing words only by spelling.) Tj
T*
(- Jumping to an answer without showing the steps or reasoning clearly.) Tj
T*
(- Practising Pronunciation without checking whether the method matches the question) Tj
T*
(being asked.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Study Tips) Tj
T*
(- Rewrite the overview of Pronunciation in your own words after studying it.) Tj
T*
(- Use short exercises built around stress patterns and sound distinctions before trying) Tj
T*
(harder tasks.) Tj
T*
(- Keep track of mistakes such as pronouncing words only by spelling and write the) Tj
T*
(correction beside each one.) Tj
T*
(- Revise Pronunciation regularly so the method behind stress, vowel sounds, consonants,) Tj
T*
(and clear articulation becomes familiar.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Practice Exercises) Tj
T*
(- Explain the overview of Pronunciation and describe how it fits into English.) Tj
T*
(- Work through an example based on contrasting minimal pairs with different vowel sounds) Tj
T*
(and explain each step.) Tj
T*
(- Describe why pronouncing words only by spelling causes errors and how to avoid it.) Tj
T*
